131
00:10:46,017 --> 00:10:48,110
Goose, Cougar's in trouble.

132
00:10:48,153 --> 00:10:50,087
Come on, Mav,
we're gettin' Low on gas.

133
00:10:50,121 --> 00:10:51,782
Let's Land this sucker.

134
00:10:53,525 --> 00:10:54,514
MERLIN: Cougar!

135
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:03,267
God damn it, Maverick.

136
00:11:03,301 --> 00:11:05,201
We got no fuel for this.

137
00:11:05,237 --> 00:11:06,568
We're going after Cougar.

138
00:11:08,173 --> 00:11:11,142
You tell him to land that plane.
That's an order.

139
00:11:11,176 --> 00:11:14,043
CONTROL: Ghost Rider,
you are instructed to land.

140
00:11:14,079 --> 00:11:15,410
Land immediately.

141
00:11:19,918 --> 00:11:23,183
Any of you boys seen
an aircraft carrier around here?

142
00:11:23,221 --> 00:11:25,883
Mav, we've got a little problem
up here.

143
00:11:25,924 --> 00:11:27,448
That MIG really screwed him up.

144
00:11:27,492 --> 00:11:29,619
I don't think
he can make it back.

145
00:11:32,397 --> 00:11:33,728
You're OK, Cougar.

146
00:11:33,765 --> 00:11:35,733
Just stay on my wing.

147
00:11:35,767 --> 00:11:37,860
I'II take you all the way in.

148
00:11:37,902 --> 00:11:39,233
Just stay with me.

149
00:11:53,952 --> 00:11:56,944
Easy, Cougar.
Just a walk in the park, buddy.

150
00:11:58,290 --> 00:11:59,757
You're a Little Low.

151
00:11:59,791 --> 00:12:02,487
You're a Little Low, Coug.

152
00:12:02,527 --> 00:12:04,461
Come on, buddy. Pull up.

153
00:12:05,730 --> 00:12:07,220
MAVERICK: Pull up, Cougar.

154
00:12:08,733 --> 00:12:09,893
That's it.

155
00:12:09,934 --> 00:12:11,231
Almost there.

156
00:12:12,404 --> 00:12:14,372
CONTROL: You're well below
glide path.

157
00:12:14,406 --> 00:12:16,601
Three quarters of a mile.
Call the ball.

158
00:12:18,243 --> 00:12:19,267
Roger ball.

159
00:12:29,621 --> 00:12:31,111
MERLIN: We're too Low, Cougar.

160
00:12:31,156 --> 00:12:32,555
We're too Low, Cougar.

161
00:12:32,590 --> 00:12:33,716
Pull up!

162
00:12:33,758 --> 00:12:35,248
Some more power!

163
00:12:36,261 --> 00:12:37,751
Come on, pull again!

164
00:12:47,939 --> 00:12:49,270
AIR BOSS JOHNSON: Come in.

165
00:12:51,609 --> 00:12:52,576
Sir.

166
00:12:52,610 --> 00:12:55,078
Cougar,
you should be in sick bay.

167
00:12:55,113 --> 00:12:56,410
What's on your mind?

168
00:12:56,448 --> 00:12:57,642
My wife and kid, sir.

169
00:12:58,850 --> 00:13:00,943
Almost orphaned him today,
without ever seeing him.

170
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:04,818
I don't know what happened
up there...

171
00:13:04,856 --> 00:13:06,483
but I was so scared.

172
00:13:06,524 --> 00:13:08,355
Come on, we've seen this before.

173
00:13:08,393 --> 00:13:09,382
No, sir.

174
00:13:11,229 --> 00:13:13,424
I'm holding on too tight.

175
00:13:13,465 --> 00:13:15,228
I've lost the edge.

176
00:13:15,266 --> 00:13:17,291
I'm sorry, sir.

177
00:13:19,170 --> 00:13:20,569
I'm sorry.

178
00:13:27,245 --> 00:13:28,405
Cougar.

179
00:13:31,416 --> 00:13:32,747
Thanks, Maverick.

180
00:13:35,086 --> 00:13:37,714
JOHNSON:
Maverick, Goose, come in here.

181
00:13:37,756 --> 00:13:39,724
MAVERICK:
What the hell's going on?

182
00:13:39,758 --> 00:13:40,782
I don't know.

183
00:13:41,860 --> 00:13:42,918
Oh, shit.

184
00:13:47,265 --> 00:13:50,257
Maverick, you just did
an incredibly brave thing.

185
00:13:52,237 --> 00:13:55,229
What you should have done
was Land your plane!

186
00:13:55,273 --> 00:13:57,241
You don't own that plane...

187
00:13:57,275 --> 00:13:58,936
the taxpayers do!

188
00:13:58,977 --> 00:14:02,105
Son, your ego is writing checks
your body can't cash.

189
00:14:02,147 --> 00:14:03,705
You've been busted...

190
00:14:03,748 --> 00:14:07,184
you lost your qualifications
as section leader three times...

191
00:14:07,218 --> 00:14:09,709
put in hack twice by me...

192
00:14:09,754 --> 00:14:12,018
with a history
of high-speed passes...

193
00:14:12,056 --> 00:14:14,388
over five air control towers...

194
00:14:14,426 --> 00:14:15,916
and one admiral's daughter!

195
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:17,484
Penny Benjamin?

196
00:14:18,563 --> 00:14:19,825
And you, asshole...

197
00:14:19,864 --> 00:14:21,729
you're Lucky to be here.

198
00:14:21,766 --> 00:14:22,960
Thank you, sir.

199
00:14:23,001 --> 00:14:24,468
And Let's not bullshit,
Maverick.

200
00:14:24,502 --> 00:14:26,970
Your family name
isn't the best in the Navy.

201
00:14:27,005 --> 00:14:29,974
You need to be doing it better
and cleaner than the rest.

202
00:14:30,008 --> 00:14:31,407
Now, what is it with you?

203
00:14:31,443 --> 00:14:35,004
Just want to serve my country,
be the best pilot in the Navy.

204
00:14:35,046 --> 00:14:36,741
Don't screw around with me,
Maverick.

205
00:14:36,781 --> 00:14:38,806
You're a hell of
an instinctive pilot.

206
00:14:38,850 --> 00:14:40,044
Maybe too good.

207
00:14:40,084 --> 00:14:42,211
I'd like to bust you,
but I can't.

208
00:14:42,253 --> 00:14:43,811
I got another problem here.

209
00:14:43,855 --> 00:14:47,985
I got to send somebody
from this squadron to Miramar.

210
00:14:48,026 --> 00:14:49,755
I've got to do something here.

211
00:14:49,794 --> 00:14:51,762
I still can't believe it.

212
00:14:51,796 --> 00:14:53,764
I got to give you
your dream shot.

213
00:14:53,798 --> 00:14:56,062
I'm gonna send you up
against the best.

214
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:59,934
You two characters
are going to Top Gun.

215
00:15:01,539 --> 00:15:03,473
For five weeks...

216
00:15:03,508 --> 00:15:05,100
you will fly against the best
fighter pilots in the world.

217
00:15:05,143 --> 00:15:07,771
You were number two.
Cougar was number one.

218
00:15:07,812 --> 00:15:10,110
Cougar lost it,
turned in his wings.

219
00:15:10,148 --> 00:15:11,945
You guys are number one.

220
00:15:13,451 --> 00:15:15,419
But you remember one thing--

221
00:15:15,453 --> 00:15:17,717
you screw up just this much...

222
00:15:17,755 --> 00:15:20,724
you'll be flying a cargo plane
full of rubber dog shit...

223
00:15:20,758 --> 00:15:22,191
out of Hong Kong.

224
00:15:22,227 --> 00:15:23,251
Yes, sir!

225
00:15:27,265 --> 00:15:29,096
That is all.

226
00:15:29,133 --> 00:15:31,533
You can tell me about the MIG
some other time.

227
00:15:31,569 --> 00:15:32,558
Gentlemen!

228
00:15:33,571 --> 00:15:35,061
Good Luck, gentlemen.

229
00:15:35,106 --> 00:15:36,573
-Thank you, sir.
-Thank you.

230
00:15:42,604 --> 00:15:43,730
SONG: Out along the edge...

231
00:15:43,772 --> 00:15:46,297
is always where I burn to be.

232
00:15:48,777 --> 00:15:52,736
The further on the edge,
the hotter the intensity.

233
00:15:54,916 --> 00:15:59,410
Highway to the danger zone.

234
00:16:00,088 --> 00:16:05,651
Gonna take you
right into the danger zone.

235
00:16:07,229 --> 00:16:12,360
Highway to the danger zone.

236
00:16:13,335 --> 00:16:18,796
Right into the danger zone...

237
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:21,866
During Korea,
the Navy kill ratio was 12 to 1.

238
00:16:21,910 --> 00:16:24,344
We shot down 12 of their jets
for every one of ours.

239
00:16:24,379 --> 00:16:27,177
During Vietnam,
that ratio fell to 3 to 1.

240
00:16:27,215 --> 00:16:29,877
Our pilots had become dependent
upon missiles.

241
00:16:29,918 --> 00:16:31,476
They had lost some
of their dogfighting skills.

242
00:16:32,487 --> 00:16:34,648
Now, Top Gun was created
to teach ACM--

243
00:16:34,689 --> 00:16:36,179
Air Combat Maneuvering.

244
00:16:36,792 --> 00:16:38,020
Dogfighting.

245
00:16:38,060 --> 00:16:39,618
This gives me a hard-on.

246
00:16:39,661 --> 00:16:42,562
By Vietnam's end,
that ratio was back to 12 to 1.

247
00:16:42,597 --> 00:16:43,621
Don't tease me.

248
00:16:43,665 --> 00:16:44,791
Blinds, please.

249
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:47,666
I'd like to take this
opportunity to introduce you...

250
00:16:47,702 --> 00:16:49,533
to our commanding officer
at Top Gun.

251
00:16:49,571 --> 00:16:51,801
The first man awarded
the Top Gun trophy.

252
00:16:51,840 --> 00:16:54,206
You will not find
a finer fighter pilot...

253
00:16:54,242 --> 00:16:55,709
anywhere in the world.

254
00:16:55,744 --> 00:16:58,542
Commander Mike Metcalf.
Call sign, Viper.

255
00:16:58,580 --> 00:17:00,172
Gentlemen...

256
00:17:01,450 --> 00:17:05,853
You are the top one percent
of all naval aviators.

257
00:17:08,023 --> 00:17:09,251
The elite.

258
00:17:09,291 --> 00:17:11,350
The best of the best.

259
00:17:11,393 --> 00:17:13,361
We'll make you better.

