01:04:36,905 --> 01:04:38,429
Metal under tension...

1035
01:04:38,473 --> 01:04:41,203
beggin' you to touch and go.

1036
01:04:43,211 --> 01:04:47,807
Highway to the danger zone.

1037
01:04:49,317 --> 01:04:55,847
Ride into the danger zone.

1038
01:04:55,890 --> 01:04:58,188
It's bottom of the ninth.
The score is tied.

1039
01:04:58,226 --> 01:04:59,693
It's time for the big one.

1040
01:04:59,728 --> 01:05:01,195
You up for this one, Maverick?

1041
01:05:01,229 --> 01:05:03,697
Just a walk in the park,
Kazansky.

1042
01:05:07,669 --> 01:05:10,194
Contact.
Multiple bogeys. 1-6-5.

1043
01:05:10,238 --> 01:05:12,570
Two miles. Looks like
they're going away from us.

1044
01:05:12,607 --> 01:05:14,040
Ho, I see them.

1045
01:05:14,075 --> 01:05:15,667
Tallyho.
Right, two o'clock. I'm in.

1046
01:05:15,710 --> 01:05:16,734
I'm in.

1047
01:05:36,664 --> 01:05:38,996
That son of a bitch
cut me off.

1048
01:05:47,175 --> 01:05:49,666
Come on, come on. Jesus Christ.

1049
01:05:49,711 --> 01:05:51,406
Ice, take the shot.

1050
01:05:51,446 --> 01:05:53,346
Ice, get the hell out of there.

1051
01:05:53,381 --> 01:05:54,678
I can't get the angle.

1052
01:05:54,716 --> 01:05:57,378
I'm too close for missiles.
I'm switching to guns.

1053
01:05:57,419 --> 01:05:59,046
Ice, fire or clear.

1054
01:06:04,993 --> 01:06:06,460
Look at this.

1055
01:06:06,494 --> 01:06:09,190
Jesus Christ, I could take
the shot right here!

1056
01:06:09,230 --> 01:06:11,323
I need another 20 seconds,
then I've got him.

1057
01:06:16,971 --> 01:06:18,768
I'm moving in.
I've got the shot.

1058
01:06:18,807 --> 01:06:20,331
Mav, let's get in there.

1059
01:06:20,375 --> 01:06:21,364
Come on, Mav.

1060
01:06:22,844 --> 01:06:25,005
Maverick's getting impatient.
Come on, take the shot.

1061
01:06:25,046 --> 01:06:26,673
Ten more seconds,
then I've got him.

1062
01:06:28,550 --> 01:06:31,542
Ice, get out of there.
Let's do it, Mav.

1063
01:06:31,586 --> 01:06:33,451
Ice, come off high right.
I'm in.

1064
01:06:33,488 --> 01:06:34,614
Five more seconds.

1065
01:06:34,656 --> 01:06:36,749
Come off high right, Ice.
I'm in.

1066
01:06:36,791 --> 01:06:38,122
I'm off him. Shit!

1067
01:06:41,529 --> 01:06:43,292
We're in his jetwash.

1068
01:06:43,331 --> 01:06:44,389
Holy shit!

1069
01:06:47,402 --> 01:06:50,269
GOOSE: This is not good.
We got a flame out back.

1070
01:06:50,305 --> 01:06:51,738
Engine one is out.

1071
01:06:51,773 --> 01:06:53,331
Engine two is out.

1072
01:06:53,374 --> 01:06:55,604
Goose, I'm losing control,
I'm losing control!

1073
01:06:55,643 --> 01:06:58,168
I can't control it.
It won't recover. Shit!

1074
01:07:00,615 --> 01:07:02,480
It's coupling up.
We're out of control.

1075
01:07:02,517 --> 01:07:04,644
This is not good.

1076
01:07:04,686 --> 01:07:06,517
ICEMAN: Mayday! Mayday!
Mav's in trouble.

1077
01:07:06,554 --> 01:07:08,715
He's in a flat spin,
heading out to sea.

1078
01:07:11,159 --> 01:07:14,560
Altitude 8,000! 7,000!

1079
01:07:15,763 --> 01:07:17,788
Six. We're at six, Mav.

1080
01:07:17,832 --> 01:07:18,821
Aah!

1081
01:07:20,435 --> 01:07:21,925
I'm pinned forward, Goose.

1082
01:07:21,970 --> 01:07:23,528
I can't reach
the ejection handle.

1083
01:07:25,306 --> 01:07:27,274
Goose, you have to punch us out.

1084
01:07:27,308 --> 01:07:29,367
I can't reach
the ejection handle.

1085
01:07:29,410 --> 01:07:30,502
Eject!

1086
01:07:30,545 --> 01:07:31,512
I'm trying.

1087
01:07:31,546 --> 01:07:33,173
Eject! Eject! Eject!

1088
01:07:33,214 --> 01:07:34,909
Watch the canopy.

1089
01:07:52,400 --> 01:07:54,027
Goose! Goose!

1090
01:07:54,068 --> 01:07:55,092
Oh, no.

1091
01:07:55,136 --> 01:07:56,228
Oh.

1092
01:07:58,139 --> 01:07:59,265
Oh, God.

1093
01:07:59,307 --> 01:08:01,241
Oh, God. Oh, God.

1094
01:08:01,276 --> 01:08:02,300
Oh.

1095
01:08:15,123 --> 01:08:17,216
Oh, God. Oh, God.

1096
01:08:47,422 --> 01:08:50,619
DIVER: Sir, let go of him.

1097
01:08:50,658 --> 01:08:52,285
You got to let him go, sir.

1098
01:09:35,460 --> 01:09:37,121
VIPER: How you doing?

1099
01:09:37,162 --> 01:09:38,720
MAVERICK: I'm all right.

1100
01:09:41,566 --> 01:09:43,033
VIPER: Goose is dead.

1101
01:09:43,068 --> 01:09:44,626
I know.

1102
01:09:48,139 --> 01:09:52,200
VIPER: You fly jets long enough
something like this happens.

1103
01:09:53,344 --> 01:09:56,802
He was my R.I.O.
My responsibility.

1104
01:09:59,818 --> 01:10:02,946
My squadron in Vietnam,
we lost 8 of 18 aircraft.

1105
01:10:02,987 --> 01:10:04,511
Ten men.

1106
01:10:04,556 --> 01:10:07,992
First one dies, you die, too.

1107
01:10:08,993 --> 01:10:11,223
But there will be others.

1108
01:10:12,230 --> 01:10:14,164
You can count on it.

1109
01:10:16,334 --> 01:10:18,666
You got to let him go.

1110
01:10:20,805 --> 01:10:23,273
You got to let him go.

1111
01:10:40,959 --> 01:10:42,722
MAVERICK:
I think maybe it was my fault.

1112
01:10:45,196 --> 01:10:46,686
I don't know.

1113
01:10:48,199 --> 01:10:51,259
I don't know
what the hell went wrong.

1114
01:10:53,204 --> 01:10:55,468
I'd like to help.

1115
01:10:56,708 --> 01:10:58,369
I know it's difficult.

1116
01:11:03,081 --> 01:11:05,379
God, I want him back.

1117
01:11:12,023 --> 01:11:15,083
I'II be here if you need me, OK?

1118
01:13:08,106 --> 01:13:10,768
God, he loved flying with you,
Maverick.

1119
01:13:28,993 --> 01:13:32,929
He'd have flown anyway...
without you.

1120
01:13:34,666 --> 01:13:38,762
He'd have hated it,
but he would have done it.

1121
01:13:59,190 --> 01:14:01,590
INQUIRY COMMANDER: We find that
the F-14 flat spin...

1122
01:14:01,626 --> 01:14:04,595
was induced
by the disruption of airflow...

1123
01:14:04,629 --> 01:14:06,096
into the starboard engine.

1124
01:14:06,130 --> 01:14:10,760
This disruption
stalled the engine...

1125
01:14:10,802 --> 01:14:13,600
which produced
enough yaw rate...

1126
01:14:13,638 --> 01:14:18,098
to induce a spin
which was unrecoverable.

1127
01:14:18,142 --> 01:14:19,609
There was no way...

1128
01:14:19,644 --> 01:14:21,111
Lieutenant Mitchell
could either see or avoid...

1129
01:14:21,145 --> 01:14:23,841
the jetwash
which produced the engine stall.

1130
01:14:23,881 --> 01:14:27,544
Therefore, the board finds
Lieutenant Pete Mitchell...

1131
01:14:27,585 --> 01:14:29,883
was not at fault
in the accident of 29 July.

1132
01:14:29,921 --> 01:14:32,185
Lieutenant Mitchell's record
is cleared of this incident.

1133
01:14:32,223 --> 01:14:36,159
Lieutenant Mitchell is restored
to flight status without delay.

1134
01:14:38,062 --> 01:14:39,689
These proceedings are closed.

1135
01:14:48,239 --> 01:14:50,867
Get him up flying soon.

1136
01:15:17,735 --> 01:15:19,828
JESTER: Come on, kid.
Get in there. Engage.

1137
01:15:19,871 --> 01:15:21,736
SUNDOWN: You got a bogey
at two o'cIock low.

1138
01:15:21,773 --> 01:15:23,741
You got the angle.
Piece of cake.

1139
01:15:27,979 --> 01:15:30,072
JESTER: Take the shot, kid.

1140
01:15:31,883 --> 01:15:33,009
SUNDOWN:
You can engage any time.

1141
01:15:43,861 --> 01:15:46,386
Hey, where the hell
are you going?

1142
01:15:46,431 --> 01:15:48,831
Uh, it's not good.
It doesn't look good.

1143
01:15:48,866 --> 01:15:52,063
It doesn't get to look
any better than that.

1144
01:16:04,682 --> 01:16:07,242
SUNDOWN: Hey, man,
we couId have had him.

1145
01:16:07,285 --> 01:16:09,344
Hey, we could have had him, man!

1146
01:16:10,955 --> 01:16:14,186
I will fire when I am
goddamn good and ready!

1147
01:16:14,225 --> 01:16:15,692
You got that?

1148
01:16:34,178 --> 01:16:36,612
JESTER: He can't get back
in the saddle. Won't engage.

1149
01:16:36,647 --> 01:16:38,945
VIPER:
It's only been a few days.

1150
01:16:38,983 --> 01:16:42,475
JESTER: You know,
he just might not make it back.

1151
01:16:45,690 --> 01:16:47,157
Keep sending him up.

1152
01:17:06,055 --> 01:17:07,545
Mitchell...

1153
01:17:09,058 --> 01:17:10,685
I'm sorry about Goose.

1154
01:17:15,064 --> 01:17:16,554
Everybody liked him.

1155
01:17:22,572 --> 01:17:24,062
I'm sorry.

1156
01:17:43,793 --> 01:17:45,590
Hi, it's Wolfman.

1157
01:17:48,598 --> 01:17:50,259
Yeah, Maverick just quit.

1158
01:18:13,389 --> 01:18:14,515
Excuse me.

1159
01:18:18,060 --> 01:18:19,527
May I?

1160
01:18:19,562 --> 01:18:20,995
Please.

1161
01:18:30,206 --> 01:18:32,538
CHARLIE:
I'II have what he's having.

1162
01:18:32,575 --> 01:18:34,406
Hemlock, is it?

1163
01:18:35,411 --> 01:18:36,742
MAVERICK: Ice water.

1164
01:18:41,584 --> 01:18:44,075
CHARLIE: You weren't going
to say good-bye?

1165
01:18:46,088 --> 01:18:49,546
I heard you got that job
in Washington.

1166
01:18:49,592 --> 01:18:51,059
Congratulations.

1167
01:18:51,093 --> 01:18:52,583
Thanks.

1168
01:18:55,097 --> 01:18:58,589
But I wasn't gonna leave
without saying good-bye.

1169
01:19:01,537 --> 01:19:03,528
It's good to see you.

1170
01:19:04,540 --> 01:19:05,529
CHARLIE: Thanks.

1171
01:19:07,543 --> 01:19:09,033
Where you going?

1172
01:19:10,546 --> 01:19:13,379
You don't even have a ticket,
do you?

1173
01:19:14,417 --> 01:19:19,013
I've seen all the evidence.
It's not your responsibility.

1174
01:19:19,055 --> 01:19:20,716
It's not your fault.

1175
01:19:22,058 --> 01:19:25,550
You're one of the best pilots
in the Navy.

1176
01:19:26,562 --> 01:19:30,054
What you do up there,
it's dangerous.

1177
01:19:31,233 --> 01:19:33,724
But you've got to go on.

1178
01:19:33,769 --> 01:19:35,828
You don't understand.

1179
01:19:37,073 --> 01:19:40,042
When I first met you...

1180
01:19:40,076 --> 01:19:42,567
you were larger than life.

1181
01:19:44,413 --> 01:19:46,040
Look at you.

1182
01:19:47,083 --> 01:19:51,076
You're not going to be happy
unless you're going mach two...

1183
01:19:51,120 --> 01:19:53,145
with your hair on fire.
You know that.

1184
01:19:53,189 --> 01:19:56,215
Naw, it's over. It's just over.

1185
01:19:56,258 --> 01:19:57,850
CHARLIE:
To be the best of the best...

1186
01:19:57,893 --> 01:20:01,226
means you make mistakes,
and then you go on.

1187
01:20:01,263 --> 01:20:02,730
It's just like the rest of us.

1188
01:20:02,765 --> 01:20:05,256
MAVERICK:
You don't think I know that?

1189
01:20:06,602 --> 01:20:09,093
I'm here to help.

1190
01:20:10,239 --> 01:20:13,072
Look, thank you.

1191
01:20:13,109 --> 01:20:18,376
But if I wanted help, really,
I would have asked for it.

1192
01:20:23,619 --> 01:20:25,610
So I'm too late.

1193
01:20:28,124 --> 01:20:29,614
You've already left.

1194
01:20:31,127 --> 01:20:34,221
You didn't learn
a damn thing, did you?

1195
01:20:35,297 --> 01:20:36,787
Except to quit.

1196
01:20:40,136 --> 01:20:43,128
You've got that maneuver down
real well.

1197
01:20:51,147 --> 01:20:53,172
So long, Pete Mitchell.

1198
01:21:15,104 --> 01:21:16,594
[Rings doorbell]

1199
01:21:18,607 --> 01:21:21,405
MRS. METCALF:
Well, hi, Maverick. Come on in.

1200
01:21:21,444 --> 01:21:24,242
-How you doing?
-Good.

1201
01:21:24,280 --> 01:21:26,908
-You sure you're feeling OK?
-Fine. Great.

1202
01:21:26,949 --> 01:21:30,749
-Can I get you a drink?
-No, thank you.

1203
01:21:30,786 --> 01:21:34,244
Make yourself comfortable.
Mike will be right down.

1204
01:21:34,290 --> 01:21:35,780
OK. Thank you.

1205
01:21:54,143 --> 01:21:56,703
I flew with your old man.

1206
01:21:56,746 --> 01:21:58,805
VF-51, the Oriskany.

1207
01:22:01,584 --> 01:22:05,577
You're a lot like he was,
only better...

1208
01:22:07,590 --> 01:22:09,080
and worse.

1209
01:22:10,593 --> 01:22:14,085
He was a natural heroic
son of a bitch, that one.

1210
01:22:16,932 --> 01:22:19,492
So, he did do it right.

1211
01:22:23,939 --> 01:22:26,464
Yeah, he did it right.

1212
01:22:35,618 --> 01:22:39,076
VIPER: Is that why you fly
the way you do...

1213
01:22:39,121 --> 01:22:40,611
trying to prove something?

1214
01:22:42,124 --> 01:22:45,116
Yeah, your old man did it right.

1215
01:22:46,629 --> 01:22:49,598
What I'm about to tell you
is classified.

1216
01:22:49,632 --> 01:22:51,657
It could end my career.

1217
01:22:51,700 --> 01:22:54,362
We were in the worst dogfight
I ever dreamed of.

1218
01:22:54,403 --> 01:22:57,964
There were bogeys like fireflies
all over the sky.

1219
01:23:00,075 --> 01:23:01,702
His F-4 was hit,
and he was wounded...

1220
01:23:01,744 --> 01:23:02,870
but he could have made it back.

1221
01:23:02,912 --> 01:23:04,072
He stayed in it.

1222
01:23:04,113 --> 01:23:06,138
Saved three planes
before he bought it.

1223
01:23:09,418 --> 01:23:10,976
MAVERICK: How come I never
heard that before?

1224
01:23:11,020 --> 01:23:13,682
That's not something the State
Department tells dependents...

1225
01:23:13,722 --> 01:23:17,249
when the battle occurred
over the wrong line on some map.

1226
01:23:18,761 --> 01:23:20,228
MAVERICK: So you were there?

1227
01:23:20,262 --> 01:23:22,093
VIPER: I was there.

1228
01:23:23,098 --> 01:23:24,656
What's on your mind?

1229
01:23:26,101 --> 01:23:28,262
My options, sir.

1230
01:23:29,605 --> 01:23:30,765
Simple.

1231
01:23:31,874 --> 01:23:34,069
First, you've acquired enough
points to show up tomorrow...

1232
01:23:34,109 --> 01:23:36,737
and graduate
with your Top Gun class...

1233
01:23:36,779 --> 01:23:38,679
or you could quit.

1234
01:23:40,816 --> 01:23:43,080
There'd be no disgrace.
That spin was hell.

1235
01:23:43,118 --> 01:23:44,915
It would've shook me up.

1236
01:23:44,954 --> 01:23:46,649
So you think I should quit?

1237
01:23:46,689 --> 01:23:48,281
I didn't say that.

1238
01:23:50,092 --> 01:23:53,584
The simple fact is you
feel responsible for Goose...

1239
01:23:53,629 --> 01:23:55,392
and you have
a confidence problem.

1240
01:23:56,999 --> 01:24:00,400
I'm not going to sit here
and bIow sunshine up your ass.

1241
01:24:00,436 --> 01:24:05,135
A good pilot is compelled
to evaluate what's happened...

1242
01:24:05,174 --> 01:24:07,005
so he can apply
what he's learned.

1243
01:24:08,577 --> 01:24:11,546
Up there, we got to push it.

1244
01:24:11,580 --> 01:24:13,047
That's our job.

1245
01:24:15,751 --> 01:24:17,548
It's your option, Lieutenant...

1246
01:24:17,586 --> 01:24:19,247
all yours.

1247
01:24:30,099 --> 01:24:33,626
Sorry to bother you
on a Sunday, sir...

1248
01:24:33,669 --> 01:24:35,364
but thank you very much
for your time.

1249
01:24:35,404 --> 01:24:38,464
VIPER: No problem. Good luck.

1250
01:25:23,052 --> 01:25:25,020
[Applause]

1251
01:25:27,423 --> 01:25:28,685
Gentlemen...

1252
01:25:28,724 --> 01:25:30,055
Where's Maverick?

1253
01:25:31,427 --> 01:25:33,327
I don't know where he is.

1254
01:25:35,030 --> 01:25:37,055
You know what
he's planning to do?

1255
01:25:38,834 --> 01:25:40,893
Got to be hard on the guy,
though, you know.

1256
01:25:40,936 --> 01:25:42,096
Good luck.

1257
01:26:02,558 --> 01:26:04,048
Hi, Mav.

1258
01:26:12,901 --> 01:26:14,698
Congratulations.

1259
01:26:14,737 --> 01:26:16,136
Thank you.

1260
01:26:17,139 --> 01:26:19,539
-Congratulations.
-Thanks, Mav.

1261
01:26:19,575 --> 01:26:20,735
Sir.

1262
01:26:23,579 --> 01:26:26,241
Gentlemen,
I hate to break up the party...

1263
01:26:26,281 --> 01:26:28,272
before it really
gets out of hand...

1264
01:26:28,317 --> 01:26:29,978
but there's work to be done.

1265
01:26:30,019 --> 01:26:32,886
Some of you have to depart
immediately.

1266
01:26:32,921 --> 01:26:35,321
We have a crisis situation.

1267
01:26:35,357 --> 01:26:37,723
-Ice, Slider!
-Yo.

1268
01:26:37,760 --> 01:26:39,352
-Hollywood, Wolfman!
-Yes, sir.

1269
01:26:41,430 --> 01:26:42,795
Maverick!

1270
01:26:42,831 --> 01:26:44,093
Sir.

1271
01:26:47,603 --> 01:26:51,403
Maverick, you'll get your R.I.O.
when you get to your ship.

1272
01:26:51,440 --> 01:26:55,399
And if you don't...
give me a call.

1273
01:26:55,444 --> 01:26:57,036
I'II fly with you.

1274
01:26:58,781 --> 01:26:59,941
Sir.

1275
01:27:09,614 --> 01:27:11,582
AIR BOSS JOHNSON:
Gentlemen, this is bull's eye.

1276
01:27:11,616 --> 01:27:13,140
The communications ship,
S.S. Layton...

1277
01:27:13,185 --> 01:27:17,451
has become disabled and wandered
into foreign territory.

1278
01:27:17,489 --> 01:27:20,322
A rescue operation
is to begin within the hour.

1279
01:27:20,358 --> 01:27:23,293
Your mission is to give
air support to that rescue.

1280
01:27:24,029 --> 01:27:26,623
There are MIGs in the area,
and tensions are high.

1281
01:27:26,665 --> 01:27:30,499
If you witness a hostile act,
you will return fire.

1282
01:27:30,535 --> 01:27:33,993
Those MIGs carry
the Exocet antiship missile.

1283
01:27:34,039 --> 01:27:36,337
They can fire them
